<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-2337] Verify that metric names will not collide when creating new topics</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2337</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When creating a new topic, convert the proposed topic name to the name that will be used in metrics and validate that there are no collisions with existing names.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See this discussion for context: &lt;a href=&quot;http://s.apache.org/snW&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://s.apache.org/snW&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


</description>
